# PATHWISE — PHASE 1: CAREER & COURSE KNOWLEDGE FOUNDATION
AND DETERMINISTIC RECOMMENDATION ARCHITECTURE

IMPORTANT CONTEXT

PathWise is an adaptive career guidance platform targeting two fundamentally
different student groups:

1. Class 10 students:
   Goal = understand interests, subjects, strengths, work preferences and
   career values, then recommend suitable academic streams/directions and
   career families to explore.

2. Class 12 students:
   Goal = understand their EXISTING stream (PCM, PCB, PCMB, Commerce with
   Maths, Commerce without Maths, Arts/Humanities, Vocational/Other), their
   interests, strengths and goals, then recommend eligible courses/degrees,
   specializations and career paths.

The existing project already contains:

- Single pnpm/Turborepo monorepo
- Next.js frontend
- Express + TypeScript MS1 Core API
- FastAPI + Python MS2 AI Engine
- PostgreSQL
- Redis
- Neo4j
- Docker
- JWT authentication
- LangGraph/LangChain integration
- Class 10 assessment
- Class 12 stream-specific assessment branches
- Approximately 10-question adaptive/structured assessments
- Stable question IDs
- Answer submission idempotency
- Assessment session persistence
- Assessment restoration/recovery architecture
- PostgreSQL assessment state synchronization
- Double-submit protection
- Results and Roadmap frontend pages

DO NOT redesign or visually modify the frontend in this phase.

DO NOT rewrite the working assessment flow.

DO NOT modify authentication unless absolutely required.

DO NOT introduce Gemini/API calls in Phase 1.

The purpose of Phase 1 is to create the reliable data and recommendation
foundation that later Gemini personalization will use.


===========================================================
PHASE 1 OBJECTIVE
===========================================================

Build a canonical Career & Course Knowledge Layer in PostgreSQL and connect
it to a deterministic recommendation/matching architecture.

The system must separate:

A. CANONICAL KNOWLEDGE
   Information that is mostly the same for every user.

B. PERSONALIZED RECOMMENDATION DATA
   Information that depends on an individual student's assessment.

Example:

CAREER:
AI/ML Engineer

Canonical information:
- Career overview
- Relevant courses
- Skills
- Career progression
- Salary ranges
- Industries
- Eligibility context

User A:
AI/ML Engineer
Match Score: 92%

User B:
AI/ML Engineer
Match Score: 81%

Both users reference the SAME canonical AI/ML Engineer record.

The match score and personalized explanation belong to the individual
user recommendation.

The canonical career details must NOT be regenerated for every user.


