This profile should be derived from ALL relevant assessment answers.

Do NOT generate this profile from only the final answer.

Do NOT use Gemini in Phase 1.

The profile must be reproducible from the same assessment answers.


===========================================================
CLASS 10 RECOMMENDATION LOGIC
===========================================================

Class 10 recommendation goals are fundamentally different from Class 12.

Class 10 primary outputs:

1. Recommended academic direction/stream
2. Alternative academic direction
3. Career families to explore

Possible academic directions:

Science — PCM
Science — PCB
Science — PCMB
Commerce
Commerce with Mathematics
Humanities / Arts
Design / Creative
Vocational / Skill-Based

The deterministic scoring engine should use:

- Subject interests
- Mathematics comfort
- Science interest
- Biology interest
- Technology interest
- Business interest
- Creative interest
- Strengths
- Work style
- Career values
- Career certainty

The system should produce match scores.

Example:

Science — PCM: 91
Commerce with Mathematics: 76
Design / Creative: 54

The exact weights must be documented in code/configuration and should be
easy to modify.

Do NOT generate fake precision.

Scores should represent internal compatibility scores, not scientific
probabilities.

The UI may display them as "Match Score" rather than claiming a literal
probability of career success.


===========================================================
CLASS 12 RECOMMENDATION LOGIC
===========================================================

Class 12 recommendations must consider:

academicStage = Class 12
currentStream
assessment profile
course eligibility
career interests
strengths
subject preferences
work style
career values

Pipeline:

Completed Assessment
        ↓
Structured Student Profile
        ↓
Eligibility Filter
        ↓
Eligible Courses
        ↓
Career/Course Candidate Matching
        ↓
Deterministic Match Scores
        ↓
Top Recommendations

Example:

Class 12 PCM student

AI/ML Engineer: 92
Data Scientist: 87
Software Engineer: 83

Associated eligible courses:

B.Tech AI & ML
B.Tech CSE
B.Tech Data Science


A PCB student may instead receive:

Medicine
Biotechnology
Pharmacy
Biomedical Sciences
Psychology
Physiotherapy

depending on their assessment answers and eligibility.


===========================================================
USER RECOMMENDATIONS
===========================================================

Recommendations must be persisted.

A user recommendation should reference canonical knowledge.

Example conceptual structure:

id
user_id
assessment_id
career_id OR academic_direction_id
match_score
personalized_reason
strength_alignment
interest_alignment
potential_gaps
generation_source
created_at

For Phase 1:

generation_source = DETERMINISTIC

Later phases may use:

generation_source = GEMINI_ENRICHED


Once recommendations are generated for a completed assessment, refreshing
the Results page must NOT regenerate them.

The system should retrieve persisted recommendations.

A new recommendation set should only be generated when:

- A new assessment is completed
- The user explicitly retakes the assessment
- The recommendation algorithm version changes and regeneration is
  intentionally requested


===========================================================
MATCH SCORING
===========================================================

Create a deterministic, explainable matching system.

Do not use random scores.

Do not use an LLM to invent scores.

Each recommendation score should be traceable to profile dimensions.

Example conceptual calculation:

AI/ML Engineer

Technology Interest       25%
Mathematics Comfort       20%
Programming Interest      20%
Analytical Strength       15%
Problem Solving           10%
Innovation Value          10%

Final internal score:
